      "text": "Great question. The memory model shifted from **append-only incident logs** to a **hybrid log + state snapshot**.\n\n### What changed\n\n- **Old format (event-log style):** chronological, dated entries (“on date X, did Y”) with no canonical “current state” object.\n- Example structure is just dated bullets at top of MEMORY.md.\n- Source: `MEMORY.md#1` and `MEMORY.md#3`\n\n- **New format (Project Status):** explicit per-project state block with:\n- **Current focus**\n- **Recent decisions**\n- **Active work**\n- plus an update timestamp.\n- Source: `MEMORY.md#501`, `MEMORY.md#503`, `MEMORY.md#505`, `MEMORY.md#510`\n\n### Retrieval failure this prevents\n\nIt prevents a **state-reconstruction failure** (and stale retrieval drift): when asked “what’s happening now?”, retrieval no longer has to infer current status from scattered historical events and risk returning old-but-similar items.\nWith `Project Status`, there is a single high-signal, recency-anchored state summary, so “current focus / active work” queries resolve to the latest intended snapshot instead of outdated log fragments.\n\n📚 _Memory: MEMORY.md#1, MEMORY.md#3, MEMORY.md#501, MEMORY.md#503, MEMORY.md#505, MEMORY.md#510_",
